    en: "Workers with disabilities have the right to reasonable accommodation at work — changes to the job, the schedule, or the workspace that allow the person to do the work. Employers must provide accommodation unless it causes undue hardship. Common accommodations include modified schedules, ergonomic equipment, work-from-home arrangements, additional breaks, and job restructuring. Many workers do not ask because they do not know they can."
